{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"82418bf2-f6b3-42ba-a757-c3811e738dbe","content":"Your `.testsettings` file is a legacy format that modern MSTest/VSTest ignores. You need to migrate to a `.runsettings` file. Here's what your settings map to:\n\n| `.testsettings` setting | `.runsettings` equivalent |\n|---|---|\n| `TestTimeout=30000` | `<MSTest><TestTimeout>30000</TestTimeout>` |\n| CodeCoverage DataCollector | `<DataCollectors>` section |\n| AssemblyResolution/LoadContext | Default behavior now — not needed |","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_0188UGY3ApnBuCWueaL6VymC","name":"create","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-b58606440baf458f9ad3ff3777322696/local.runsettings","file_text":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<RunSettings>\n  <MSTest>\n    <TestTimeout>30000</TestTimeout>\n    <DeploymentEnabled>false</DeploymentEnabled>\n  </MSTest>\n  <DataCollectionRunSettings>\n    <DataCollectors>\n      <DataCollector friendlyName=\"Code Coverage\"\n        uri=\"datacollector://Microsoft/CodeCoverage/2.0\"\n        assemblyQualifiedName=\"Microsoft.VisualStudio.TraceCollector.dll\">\n        <Configuration>\n          <CodeCoverage>\n            <ModulePaths>\n              <Exclude>\n                <ModulePath>.*tests.*\\.dll$</ModulePath>\n              </Exclude>\n            </ModulePaths>\n          </CodeCoverage>\n        </Configuration>\n      </DataCollector>\n    </DataCollectors>\n  </DataCollectionRunSettings>\n</RunSettings>\n"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"create a new file at /tmp/sv-b58606440baf458f9ad3ff3777322696/local.runsettings."}],"interactionId":"a4e3a715-fd20-4f07-9e8e-07765aab74b1","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has an MSTest v3 project with a `.testsettings` file. `.testsettings` files are a legacy format that is no longer supported by modern MSTest / VSTest. They need to migrate to a `.runsettings` file.\n\nLet me look at the `.testsettings` file:\n1. Assembly resolution with `useLoadContext=\"true\"` - this is default behavior in modern MSTest\n2. `TestTimeout` property set to 30000ms (30 seconds)\n3. Code Coverage data collector\n\nI need to create an equivalent `.runsettings` file. Let me create one.\n\nFor MSTest v3:\n\n\n- Test timeout goes into the `.runsettings` file under the MSTest section, and I can also use the `[Timeout]` attribute on test methods\n- Code coverage configuration moves to the data collectors section\n- Assembly resolution and deployment work differently in the modern format\n\nI'll create the `.runsettings` file and update the project file to reference it.","outputTokens":708,"requestId":"7C13:16BC0E:18E1652:1C338BD:69F95990"},"id":"e656e531-1850-42d3-a3f6-b6cda6c53ace","timestamp":"2026-05-05T02:44:46.521Z","parentId":"717b9b60-2cd3-4afd-abbb-abde3ae7f38a"}
